#	This file contains config info for /config/ra_alerts object.The format for the file is defined as:
#	The line starting with # defines comment

#	The first noncommented line is expected to be "version" number.
#	Every Alert information should start with the identifier RA_Alert:(The word is case sensitive).

# 	Following the Alert identifier is the name of the Alert , sender name and locale name of the alert.
#	The above said should be in  the same line.

#	The next line after Alertidentifier is the Email addr and email type  and these should be in the same line.
#	Valid fields for email addr type is 1(Mail_To), 2(CC), 3(BCC), 4(Reply_To).
#	Email Type is optional and if not specified will be taken as 1.
#	The field delimiter in a line may be space or tab.

#	Space or tab is not allowed in a single field.
#	A sample format is given below

#	RA_Alert:  <Alert Name>  <Sender Name> <Locale>
# 	<Email_addr 1> <Email Type> 
#	<Email_addr 2> <Email Type> 
#	<Email_addr 3> <Email Type> 

#	RA_Alert:  <Alert Name>  <Sender Name> <Locale>
# 	<Email_addr 1> <Email Type> 
#	<Email_addr 2> <Email Type> 
#	<Email_addr 3> <Email Type> 


